node.text: We all love those all white leaves on our variegated Monsteras and Syngoniums, etc, but we need to perform some maintenance on some of our variegated plants! node.text:
🪴This Cast Iron Plant has a story, and often times, it is the story that makes the plant extra special. 
🪴When my grandmother came to Italy in 1968, she took a piece of a cast iron plant (from her town’s medieval church) with her to the U.S.  Growing up in Ohio, I always remembered seeing this plant in her house. When I bought my first home, she divided her plant and gave me a piece...and it was probably about 17 or 18 years ago. She has since passed, but it is a constant reminder of her and the town my family is from. 🙏🏻
🪴Do you have any special plants with stories?  Cast Iron Plants are wonderful, lower light plants that can take a beating and are pretty underrated in my opinion! There are some beautiful variegated varieties, but I love my plain green plant 💚
.
.
.
.
.

💦When you’re diluting a fertilizer with water, it is important to always read the label and measure both the fertilizer and water amounts correctly.
💦Never eyeball any amounts. If your solution turns out too weak, this is not an issue, but if it’s too concentrated, you are at risk of fertilizer burn. 
💦So measure away! I like to use dedicated kitchen measuring spoons that I only use for fertilizing, and I use a gallon jug to measure water. This way I know I have the correct concentration. 
.
.
.
.
.

node.text:
🪴String of Pearls enjoyings its best life outdoors 🥰 Anytime you are moving a houseplant from indoors to outdoors, always move it into complete shade first (even for sun loving plants like this). They need to slowly become accustomed to the higher light outdoors. Once in shade for a while, you can start to slowly increase any direct sun exposure. Moving indoor plants straight into full sun outside will quickly cause them to scald (often in a matter of hours). Slowly but surely is the way to go. 
🪴Has anyone ever burned a plant this way? I’ve seen a lot of people do this and not know what happened, so this is your public service announcement 😊📣📢 I elaborate on this topic in my book coming out this March! 📚 
.
.
.
.
.

🖤Colocasia antiquorum ‘Black Beauty’ in my garden.  I love the tropical flair it adds to my garden in Ohio! The amazing part about Colocasia plants is that they thrive in areas that few plants will.
🖤I have this patch planted in an area with heavy clay soil and poor drainage, and it gets mostly dappled sun all day. They thrive in crappy, wet soil 😂 No drainage? No problem.  How many garden plants can you say that about? 🤷🏻‍♂️ I always preach “right plant for the right space” whether it is indoors or outdoors!
🖤Anyone else like planting Colocasia in your garden? They’re such remarkable (and versatile!) garden plants.

node.text:
🪴I haven’t shown myself in a while so here I am 😂🤷🏻‍♂️ I wanted to share today my plant story, and also wanted to find out about yours and how you got started with houseplants. 

I've been growing plants for as long as I can remember, literally.  My Italian family was always really into gardening and plants have always been part of my life.  From outdoor gardens full of all sorts of annuals and perennials (many of which I started from seed), to vegetable gardens and houseplants, nature has been an integral part of my life since I was a small child.

As far as my houseplant journey goes, I started accumulating houseplants before high school!  I loaded up a huge southern facing window with so many 😂 I'm sure we all know this now, but at the time (and it was longer ago than you might think, haha), I had read somewhere that houseplants clean your air.  My dad smoked heavily when I was growing up and I hated it..., and thus it all started and I started growing everything in sight to clean my air🤷🏻‍♂️. I also had a really fun great aunt who was constantly propagating (maybe that's where I get that from!)

So that’s how the houseplant hoarding started (and WAY before social media), and continues decades later.  How did your journey begin?  Tell me in the comments and tag a friend!

Also, my book is on its way and coming along! I will share more details on timing when preorder is available! The book will launch late this winter and I’m super excited!
